[normal]Carers UK believes [bold]it is deeply unfair for carers to both be subject to the household benefit cap and subject to [bold]new Council Tax charges. D[bold]oing so sends out a very negative message about the value the Government places on caring[bold] and may[bold] lead to family finances collapsing and caring becoming financially untenable.[bold] We continue to call on the Government to exempt Carer’[bold]s Allowance from the cap[bold] and to reconsider adding carers as a protected group within Council Tax reductions schemes. At the least, new guidance should be issued to councils on making carers[bold] a[bold] priority group for support within local reductions schemes.[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]30 September  2013[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;[bold]&#xa0;
